  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Simmias, of Rhodes, Alexandrian poet and grammarian c. 300 BC (Suda s.v. Σ. Ῥόδιος).
    Among his most important works are the Γλῶσσαι/Glôssai ('Glosses', 3 books) and a collection of poetry (Ποιήματα διάφορα/Poiḗmata diáphora, 4 books), 
    both surviving in only few fragments. S. is considered to be the inventor of technopaígnia and several lyric metres....."
    Baumbach, Manuel (Zürich). "Simias." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider. Brill, 2009.</mads:note>
